4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO WEATHER
5 MODIFICATION; PROHIBITING WEATHER MODIFICATION THAT IS NOT FOR AGRICULTURAL
6 PURPOSES; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; AND PROVIDING AN EXCEPTION; AND AMENDING SECTIONS
7 85-3-101, 85-3-102, 85-3-103, 85-3-202, AND 85-3-206, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Prohibiting weather modification. (1) Except as prescribed in 85-3-101
12 through 85-3-424, a person may not intentionally inject, release, or disperse chemicals, chemical compounds,
13 substances, or apparatuses within the borders of Montana from an aircraft expressly for:
14 (a) engaging in weather modification and control;
15 (b) affecting temperature; or
16 (c) affecting the intensity of the sunlight.
17 (2) As used in this section:
18 (a) "aircraft" means any manned or unmanned aerial vehicle or devise that is used or intended to
19 be used for flight in the air;
20 (a)(b) "chemical compounds" means any combination of any number of chemicals;
21 (b)(c) "chemicals" means industrial substances, whether simple, compound, or obtained through the
22 process of the science and art of chemistry, whether of organic or inorganic origin; and
23 (c)(d) "weather modification and control" means changing or controlling or attempting to change or
24 control, by artificial methods, the natural development of atmospheric cloud forms or precipitation forms that
25 occur in the troposphere.
